This paper is primarily focused on optimization algorithms for machine learning problems, which is a core topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses distributed optimization, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper proposes a communication-efficient framework, which is related to the field of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the concept of Federated Optimization/Learning, which is related to the field of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a framework for solving optimization problems while alleviating privacy concerns, which is related to the field of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
